    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-10-05T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-10-05T09:00:00-05:00" n="877"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d877">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.1928/437: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Panama</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-05T09:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 5, 1935—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>139. Your 59, October 3, 5 p.m. The Minister for Foreign Affairs stated yesterday
                    that inasmuch as the Panaman Commissioners leave for the United States on
                    October 7th, there is not now sufficient time to hold the discussions he had
                    suggested.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Summerlin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
